OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F309A1773493903
OL,3,CUS eases Russian oil sanctions as Iran
OL,4,Cthreatens to keep Strait of Hormuz
OL,5,Cclosed
OL,7,FThe US has eased its sanctions on
OL,8,FRussia in response to spiking oil
OL,9,Fprices, allowing nations to buy from
OL,10,FMoscow to "promote stability in global
OL,11,Fenergy markets".
OL,13,FDonald Trump's decision comes as
OL,14,FIran's continued attempts to stop
OL,15,Fshipping in the Strait of Hormuz have
OL,16,Fled to trade in the critical shipping
OL,17,Flane all but collapsing.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,310,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30902
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F309A1773493903
OL,3,CUS eases Russian oil sanctions as Iran
OL,4,Cthreatens to keep Strait of Hormuz
OL,5,Cclosed
OL,7,FOil crept back up over $100 a barrel
OL,8,Fon Thursday, leading to a fall in
OL,9,Fstock markets and putting pressure on
OL,10,FTrump to stop the conflict before
OL,11,Fserious economic damage is dealt.
OL,13,FBefore the war, a barrel of oil was
OL,14,Ftrading for between $60-$70.
OL,16,FUS Treasury Department Secretary Scott
OL,17,FBessent said the easing of sanctions
OL,18,Fwas a temporary measure to "promote
OL,19,Fstability in global energy markets"
OL,20,Fand would last until April 11.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,310,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30903
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F309A1773493903
OL,3,CUS eases Russian oil sanctions as Iran
OL,4,Cthreatens to keep Strait of Hormuz
OL,5,Cclosed
OL,7,FHe said: "This narrowly tailored,
OL,8,Fshort-term measure applies only to oil
OL,9,Falready in transit and will not
OL,10,Fprovide significant financial benefit
OL,11,Fto the Russian government."
OL,13,FThe pressure on the global oil market
OL,14,Fled to all 32 International Energy
OL,15,FAgency's (IEA) members, including the
OL,16,FUK, the US, and many of the world's
OL,17,Frichest nations, agreeing to release
OL,18,F400 million barrels of oil from their
OL,19,Freserves to combat the rise in prices,
OL,20,Fbut it only equates to around four
OL,21,Fdays' of the world's global supply.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,310,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30904
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F309A1773493903
OL,3,CUS eases Russian oil sanctions as Iran
OL,4,Cthreatens to keep Strait of Hormuz
OL,5,Cclosed
OL,7,FThe pressure in the market has also
OL,8,Fled Chancellor Rachel Reeves and
OL,9,FEnergy Secretary Ed Miliband to issue
OL,10,Fstern warnings against profiteering
OL,11,Ffrom fuel forecourts.
OL,13,FThe government has already promised to
OL,14,Fintervene if companies engage in
OL,15,F"unfair" practices that would hit
OL,16,Fcustomers facing a rise in the price
OL,17,Fof home heating oil, which is not
OL,18,Fcovered by Ofgem's energy price cap.
OL,20,FUS refuelling plane crashes in Iraq
OL,26,@wD@AOUwD@HO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/8
